Write Playwright tests that capture screenshot baselines for visual regression detection.

Create `tests/playwright/uat/visual-regression.spec.ts`:

1. For each major admin page, capture a full-page screenshot at 1920x1080
2. Store baselines in `tests/playwright/uat/baselines/`
3. On subsequent runs, compare against baselines using Playwright's `toHaveScreenshot()`
4. Threshold: 2% pixel difference allowed (minor rendering variations)

```typescript
test.describe('Visual Regression UAT', () => {
  test.use({ viewport: { width: 1920, height: 1080 } });

  test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
    await loginAsAdmin(page);
  });

  test('Dashboard — visual baseline', async ({ page }) => {
    await navigateTo(page, 'monitoring');
    await waitForData(page);
    await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('dashboard.png', { maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.02 });
  });

  test('Participants — visual baseline', async ({ page }) => {
    await navigateTo(page, 'participants');
    await waitForData(page);
    await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('participants.png', { maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.02 });
  });

  // 10 critical pages with visual baselines
});
```

Also test at 1024px width for tablet responsiveness.

Acceptance: Baselines captured for 10+ pages. Comparison mechanism works.
